By Sani Abdulrahman Kaduna – A housewife, Fatima Kano, on Tuesday dragged her former husband before a Sharia Court ll, sitting in Magajin Gari, Kaduna state, seeking N504,000 as upkeep allowance for her four children for seven years. Kano, told the court that her husband, Inuwa Abdullahi, divorced her seven years ago. She said that the court in May 2012,  ordered her ex-husband to pay N6,000 monthly for the four  children’s upkeep. The defendant, Abdullahi, a businessman who lives within Kaduna metropolis, through his counsel, Ismail Uwais, accepted the complainant’s claim. He however said that his client made an appeal at Upper Sharia court in 2014 and they couldn’t reach the complainant with the appeal summons. The Judge, Murtala Nasir, after listening to both parties, ordered the defendant to reach the complainant with the appeal sermon.